EA, G. . Technology Enhanced Mulsemedia Learning: Insights of an Evaluation. In: Computer-Human Interaction Research and Applications - CHIRA 2023, 2023, Rome, Italy. In: da Silva, H.P., Cipresso, P. (eds) Computer-Human Interaction Research and Applications. CHIRA 2023. Communications in Computer and Information Science. Cham: Spinger, 2023. v. 1997. p. 24-42. </span></div><br class="clear"><br class="clear"><div class="layout-cell layout-cell-1 text-align-right"><div class="layout-cell-pad-6 text-align-right"><b>5. </b></div></div><div class="layout-cell layout-cell-11"><span class="transform"><a class="icone-producao icone-doi" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1109/iwcmc55113.2022.9824729" target="_blank" tabindex="242"></a>BALDI, ALESSANDRO M. ; <a class="tooltip" title="Clique para visualizar o currículo" href="http://lattes.cnpq.br/6705424425518474" target="_blank" tabindex="243">CELESTRINI, JORDANO R.</a> ; ANDREAO, RODRIGO V. ; MOTA, VINICIUS F. S. ; <b>Santos, Celso A. S.</b> . A Blockchain Approach for eHealth Situation-Aware Data Processing. In: 2022 International Wireless Communications and Mobile Computing (IWCMC), 2022, Dubrovnik. 2022 International Wireless Communications and Mobile Computing (IWCMC). Los Alamitos, USA: IEEE, 2022. v. 1. p. 1040-1045. </span></div><br class="clear"><br class="clear"><div class="layout-cell layout-cell-1 text-align-right"><div class="layout-cell-pad-6 text-align-right"><b>6. </b></div></div><div class="layout-cell layout-cell-11"><span class="transform"><a class="icone-producao icone-doi" href="http://dx.doi.org/10.5753/sensoryx.2022.20005" target="_blank" tabindex="244"></a>SILVEIRA, ALEPH CAMPOS DA ; <b>SANTOS, Celso Alberto Saibel</b> . Ongoing Challenges of Evaluating Mulsemedia QoE. In: Workshop on Multisensory Experiences, 2022, Portugal. Proceedings of the 2nd Workshop on Multisensory Experiences (SensoryX 2022). Porto Alegre-RS, Brazil: Brazilian Computing Society, 2022. </span></div><br class="clear"><br class="clea